22:30.133 --> 22:31.767
So, where are you assigning me?

22:31.834 --> 22:34.233
Unit B?
Solitary?

22:34.300 --> 22:36.166
Death row?
- Somewhere you'll be safe.

22:36.233 --> 22:38.000
[buzzer]
- If you'd all just get

22:38.066 --> 22:39.734
into one line, I will take care
of everybody one at a time.

22:39.800 --> 22:41.667
- She ain't got I.D.
- I understand that, sir,

22:41.734 --> 22:43.133
but I can't let you in
without your I.D.

22:43.200 --> 22:44.734
Ma'am, I'll be with you
in one second.

22:44.800 --> 22:46.600
One second, please--if you
could just get into one line.

22:46.667 --> 22:48.433
- Think you could do something?
- Yeah, if you could just

22:48.500 --> 22:51.667
put down your first--your--
just your entire name, sir.

22:51.734 --> 22:53.266
Thank you very much.
One second, ma'am.

22:53.333 --> 22:55.600
- Listen, listen.
- Yes, your entire name.

22:55.667 --> 22:57.567
[babies crying]
[overlapping shouting]

23:00.266 --> 23:02.066
- You're the new girl.

23:02.133 --> 23:03.867
- Girl?

23:03.934 --> 23:06.300
- Yeah, you know.

23:06.367 --> 23:08.667
I'm Diane Whittlesey.

23:08.734 --> 23:11.133
- Claire Howell.

23:11.200 --> 23:13.300
- How was your first day?

23:13.367 --> 23:15.266
- Uneventful.

23:17.033 --> 23:19.100
- That's good.

23:19.166 --> 23:20.300
- I don't know.

23:20.367 --> 23:22.967
I like a little action.

23:23.033 --> 23:25.166
- Yeah, just wait.

23:25.233 --> 23:26.934
- Speaking of action.

23:27.000 --> 23:30.433
Who's the cute guy
who's running Emerald City?

23:30.500 --> 23:31.533
- Tim McManus?

23:31.600 --> 23:34.467
- He available?

23:34.533 --> 23:37.500
- Yeah, far as I know.

23:37.567 --> 23:41.133
- What?
You used to fuck him?

23:42.867 --> 23:45.367
- Yeah, actually, I did.

23:47.667 --> 23:48.834
So, if there's anything
you need,

23:48.900 --> 23:51.900
don't hesitate to ask me.

23:51.967 --> 23:54.200
- Don't you worry
about me, honey.

23:54.266 --> 23:55.734
I can take care of myself.

23:55.800 --> 23:58.433
♪ ♪

23:58.500 --> 24:00.767
- Oh, yes, I'm sure you can.

24:00.834 --> 24:01.900
♪ ♪

24:03.567 --> 24:04.500
- [knocks on door]

24:04.567 --> 24:06.333
- Mm-hmm?
- Hi.

24:06.400 --> 24:08.066
Claire Howell.
We met earlier.

24:08.133 --> 24:09.967
- Oh, yeah, yeah.
Hi.

24:10.033 --> 24:11.834
- Working late?
- No.

24:11.900 --> 24:14.333
I'm just finished,
as a matter of fact.

24:14.400 --> 24:15.867
- Want to have dinner?

24:15.934 --> 24:17.533
- Huh?

24:17.600 --> 24:20.700
- Would you like
to have dinner with me?

24:22.667 --> 24:25.500
- I, uh...

24:25.567 --> 24:26.767
- Don't tell me
you're the kind of guy

24:26.834 --> 24:29.533
who can't handle
a woman askin' him out.

24:29.600 --> 24:30.967
- Uh, no, no, no.

24:31.033 --> 24:34.600
Uh, as a matter of fact,
I-I find it kind of ballsy.

24:34.667 --> 24:36.834
- So, what do you say?

24:36.900 --> 24:38.300
There's a Romanian restaurant
around the corner

24:38.367 --> 24:40.233
I've been dying to try.

24:40.300 --> 24:43.133
- Romanian, huh?

24:43.200 --> 24:46.533
Well, why not?

24:46.600 --> 24:48.633
- I'll meet you
in the parking lot.

24:48.700 --> 24:50.100
- Okay.

24:52.033 --> 24:54.967
- And you see, love...

24:55.033 --> 24:59.000
love is the ultimate half-truth.

24:59.066 --> 25:02.133
[overlapping chatter]

25:03.433 --> 25:06.467
[all speaking Spanish]

25:10.233 --> 25:12.000
- Hey.
I missed you.

25:12.066 --> 25:13.667
Hi.

25:13.734 --> 25:16.033
[all speaking Spanish]

25:16.100 --> 25:19.500
- Sit, sit.

25:19.567 --> 25:21.367
But...

25:21.433 --> 25:23.166
hey, where's Mommy?

25:25.200 --> 25:27.967
- Oh, she couldn't come.
- Yeah, she's got the flu.

25:28.033 --> 25:29.333
- Yeah.
- She sends her love.

25:29.400 --> 25:31.700
- And this.
- This place is fucked up, man.

25:31.767 --> 25:32.967
- It don't look so bad to me.

25:33.033 --> 25:34.467
- You're in that special unit,
right?

25:34.533 --> 25:36.166
- Yeah, but it's nice,
you know?

25:36.233 --> 25:38.667
Clean.
They call it Emerald City.

25:38.734 --> 25:41.667
- They had the riot in there.
- That was like two years ago.

25:41.734 --> 25:44.600
- Even so--
- [speaking Spanish]

25:44.667 --> 25:46.033
It's gonna be fine.
- Yeah, yeah, yeah.

25:46.100 --> 25:48.900
Don't worry about me.
Okay?

25:48.967 --> 25:50.400
Don't worry about me.

25:50.467 --> 25:54.900
♪ ♪

25:54.967 --> 25:56.066
- Carlo.

25:56.133 --> 25:57.633
You had a good visit
with your family?

25:57.700 --> 25:59.066
- Yeah.
They brought these.

25:59.133 --> 26:01.400
- All right.
It's good to have family, man.

26:01.467 --> 26:03.400
- Yeah, I don't know.

26:03.467 --> 26:05.400
- You don't know what?

26:05.467 --> 26:07.767
- I don't know.

26:07.834 --> 26:09.233
- You don't know what?

26:09.300 --> 26:12.066
- I don't know what it is
to have family, man.

26:12.133 --> 26:13.867
- Wait.

26:13.934 --> 26:15.667
You saying a guy
don't need a family?

26:15.734 --> 26:17.734
- Hey, I didn't need one.

26:17.800 --> 26:20.934
Got sent to juvie when I was
nine years old for five years.

26:21.000 --> 26:23.633
Got out and got sent back up

26:23.700 --> 26:26.467
till I was about,
what, 18?

26:26.533 --> 26:29.066
Then I got sent to Lardner,
15 years.

26:29.133 --> 26:33.066
So by the time I got out,
my family was either dead, gone,

26:33.133 --> 26:34.400
or they didn't want nothin'
to do with me.

26:34.467 --> 26:37.500
- Oh, my baby,
you spent your whole life.

26:37.567 --> 26:39.734
You were raised
by the system.

26:39.800 --> 26:41.934
- Guess what, man,
I'm proud of it.

26:42.033 --> 26:43.000
- You're proud of it?

26:43.066 --> 26:44.300
- You want to play?
Here.

26:44.367 --> 26:46.300
♪ ♪

26:46.367 --> 26:48.367
- I swear to tell the truth,
the whole truth,

26:48.433 --> 26:52.333
and nothing but the truth,
so help me, God.

26:52.400 --> 26:55.800
So help me...God.

26:55.867 --> 26:58.734
So help me, God.

26:59.967 --> 27:02.533
- What do you got there?
- What?

27:02.600 --> 27:05.166
- That letter you just pocketed.
What's in it?

27:05.233 --> 27:06.533
- What letter?

27:06.600 --> 27:09.734
♪ ♪

27:09.800 --> 27:11.200
- I saw you.

27:11.266 --> 27:12.900
- Get glasses, man.

27:12.967 --> 27:14.633
- All right, give it to me.

27:14.700 --> 27:16.000
- Got nothing to give.

27:16.066 --> 27:18.266
- Listen, Hoyt.

27:18.333 --> 27:20.800
You want to start pulling scams
in here behind my back,

27:20.867 --> 27:22.100
I'll get you transferred
out of here faster

27:22.166 --> 27:23.633
than you can fucking spit.

27:23.700 --> 27:26.633
- [snorts and spits]

27:26.700 --> 27:31.367
♪ ♪

27:31.433 --> 27:32.900
- You have to do something
for me.

27:32.967 --> 27:34.533
[echoing]
For me. For me.

27:34.600 --> 27:37.800
♪ ♪

27:37.867 --> 27:42.400
- [stammering]
Ryan! Ryan!

27:42.467 --> 27:44.467
- Hey, hey.
Hey, hey.

27:44.533 --> 27:48.333
Shh, shh.

27:48.400 --> 27:50.000
Shh, it's okay.
It's okay.

27:50.066 --> 27:52.467
Did you have
that bad dream again, hmm?

27:52.533 --> 27:54.467
Yeah?
Yeah?

27:54.533 --> 27:55.834
Did you?

27:55.900 --> 27:57.266
- [crying]

27:57.333 --> 27:59.233
- No, shh, it's okay.

27:59.300 --> 28:00.667
Come here.
Come here.

28:00.734 --> 28:02.300
It's okay.
It's okay.

28:02.367 --> 28:04.700
- [sobbing]
- It's okay.

28:04.767 --> 28:06.934
It's okay, it's okay.
Don't worry about it.

28:07.000 --> 28:10.033
[overlapping chatter]

28:13.433 --> 28:14.934
No.

28:20.567 --> 28:21.867
Fuck off.

28:21.934 --> 28:24.867
- It's your job to serve me.

28:24.934 --> 28:26.934
[tongs clang]

28:31.200 --> 28:32.367
- Fuck!

28:36.133 --> 28:37.734
- And what is your problem, man?

28:37.800 --> 28:39.467
- Leave me the fuck alone.

28:39.533 --> 28:41.767
- I wish I could, man.
I got potatoes to peel.

28:41.834 --> 28:44.600
♪ ♪

28:44.667 --> 28:45.967
Oh, I see.

28:46.033 --> 28:47.900
This little hissy fit's
about Schillinger.

28:47.967 --> 28:49.300
You ain't get a chance
to make him pay

28:49.367 --> 28:50.700
for porking your brother, huh?

28:50.767 --> 28:53.333
- Fuck you, Arnold.
- [laughs]

28:53.400 --> 28:55.166
Why don't you just throw
some ground glass in his food

28:55.233 --> 28:58.934
like you did to Nino Schibetta?

28:59.000 --> 29:00.066
He's still dead.

29:00.133 --> 29:02.133
♪ ♪

29:02.200 --> 29:03.800
- Adebisi killed Nino.

29:03.867 --> 29:05.734
- Mm-hmm, yeah.

29:05.800 --> 29:07.266
- I mean,
I'd fucking airhole him,

29:07.333 --> 29:09.667
but he's always got the Aryans
or the bikers around him.

29:09.734 --> 29:12.867
I just can't get
fucking close.

29:12.934 --> 29:15.700
- Unless...

29:15.767 --> 29:19.033
- Unless?

29:19.100 --> 29:20.867
Who knew?
You think like I do.

29:20.934 --> 29:23.233
- [laughs]
That's a scary thought.

29:23.300 --> 29:26.033
♪ ♪

29:26.100 --> 29:28.233
- [knocks on door]
Hey, Jaz.

29:28.300 --> 29:29.734
I need an ask.

29:29.800 --> 29:31.633
- Don't do asks.

29:31.700 --> 29:33.066
- All right,
then how about a trade?

29:33.133 --> 29:35.433
Tits for tat?
- Talk to me.

29:35.500 --> 29:37.767
- This'll get you in deep shit
with Schillinger, man.

29:37.834 --> 29:40.266
- Fuck Schillinger.
- All right.

29:40.333 --> 29:42.300
I got a package coming in
on Thursday.

29:42.367 --> 29:43.633
I need you to slide it
through the X-ray

29:43.700 --> 29:45.533
without Big Brother
seeing what's inside.

29:45.600 --> 29:47.734
- No problem.
